# Candidate Profile (Human-Readable)

This is the plain-English version of `profile.json`. Both files should stay in sync. The JSON is what the agent reads; this is for you to review and edit.

---

## Identity

- **Name:** Jane Doe
- **Location:** Your City, State/Province, Country
- **Timezone:** America/New_York
- **Website:** https://your-website.com
- **GitHub:** https://github.com/your-username
- **LinkedIn:** https://www.linkedin.com/in/your-profile/

---

## Hard Constraints

These are automatic disqualifiers. Any job that fails ANY of these gets a score of 0.

- **Remote only.** Exception: hybrid is acceptable for [your city] roles at large companies. No relocation.
- **Salary floor:** $XXX,XXX USD / $XXX,XXX CAD (adjust to your numbers)
- **Seniority:** Intermediate and senior only. Reject intern, co-op, and entry-level.
- **Disqualifying keywords:** "on-site required", "relocation required", "intern", [add your own]
- **Disqualifying role types:** Role Type A (reason it doesn't fit), Role Type B (reason), [add your own]

---

## Language Flag

If you speak a second language, configure how the agent treats roles requiring it. Example: French is an asset, not a liability. Only flag if a role requires native-level technical writing beyond your proficiency.

---

## Security Clearance Flag

Configure based on your citizenship and clearance eligibility:

- **Clearance obtainable in your country** -> score normally
- **Allied nation clearance** -> flag, don't reject
- **Foreign clearance requiring citizenship you don't have** -> hard reject

---

## Work Authorization (US)

The agent understands these scenarios for non-US remote workers:

- **1099 contractor** -> score normally. No work auth needed.
- etc.
- **Boilerplate rule:** "Must be authorized to work in the US" is often HR boilerplate. Never auto-reject on that phrase alone.

---

## Relocation Plan (Optional)

If you plan to relocate, configure the agent to boost roles in your target region:

- Companies in your target country: highest priority
- Same-timezone roles: also valuable
- Remote jobs from your current country also work from the target country
- Remove this section if you have no relocation plans

---

## Preferences (Weighted Scoring Signals)

These don't disqualify but affect the score. Higher weight = more impact.

**Strong positives (weight 2-3):**
- Direct match to your primary skill area (weight 3)
- Pays in preferred currency (weight 2)
- Remote-first company culture (weight 2)
- [add your own signals with weights]

**Mild positives:**
- Open-source friendly
- Technical blog culture
- [add your own]

**Negatives:**
- Requires skills outside your core strength (weight -1)
- Heavy focus on tools you haven't used in production (weight -2)
- [add your own with weights]

**Work style note:** Customize the negatives to match what you want to avoid. The weights are relative, not absolute.

---

## Target Roles

**Ideal titles:** [Your ideal title 1], [Your ideal title 2], [Your ideal title 3]

**Acceptable titles:** [Your acceptable title 1], [Your acceptable title 2]

**Avoid titles:** [Title you don't want 1], [Title you don't want 2]

---

## Skills for Matching

**Strong match:** [Your core skill 1], [Your core skill 2], [Your core skill 3]

**Working knowledge:** [Skill you can use but don't lead with 1], [Skill 2]

**Not claimed:** [Skill jobs often require that you don't have 1], [Skill 2]

---

## Experience Summary

- **Years in IT:** X+
- **Years in AI/ML:** X+
- **Years LLM-specific:** X+
- **Current role:** Your Title at Your Company. Brief description.
- **Highlight projects:** List 2-4 projects with concrete numbers
- **Notable background:** Previous roles, degrees, certifications
